args:
The party defeats Thanatos, and Felicia dances
during the ensuing celebration to show her
gratitude. Phantom is flummoxed when Mym
correctly guesses at his feelings for Felicia,
and is fraught with worry the next morning
as the group sets off to return her home.
Are we back from Thanatos's realm?
Yes. He is well and truly defeated.
That means you can finally return\nto your village, Felicia.
Oh, thank you all so much!
How can I ever repay you?
Seeing you freed is reward enough.
Now all we gotta do is getcha home.
All right, everyone. Dinner is ready.
This may be the last dinner we have\nwith Felicia and Phantom.
Yes, we should reach my village tomorrow.
I can't believe how far you've come—\nand how you've continued to protect\nme even after we laid Thanatos low.
We don't know what's out there,\nso we're going to stay with you\nuntil you get to your front door.
I really can't thank you all enough.
Er, and if you don't mind, might I perform\na dance for you?
I've been wondering just how\nto thank you in my own way.
And as dancing is my one true talent,\nI'd like to do that for you.
It is a dance of prayer, offered in the\nhope of a better future.
O sky, grant unto us the light of glory!\nO soil, grant unto us the blessing of earth!
I pray forth for the prosperity of these\npeople before me. For sky and soil,\nI dedicate this dance to thee!
We should be thanking you.\nThat was wonderful.
Er, Phantom? Where are you going?
Perhaps thanks to your dance, my heart\nfeels rather lighter—and yet I suddenly\nfind myself quite exhausted.
He has been dedicating his every waking\nthought and action to protecting Felicia,\nso fatigue is understandable.
By all means, then, please rest.\nEr, but before you go...?
Thank you. For protecting me, I mean.
It was a selfish act, in the end.\n...At any rate, your dancing was divine.
From this point on, you may dance\nas your heart wills you.
Well then, good night to you.\nPleasant dreams, Phantom.
If you looked any more grave,\nI could stick a corpse in you.
I just wanted to talk to someone\nobstinate and pigheaded.
Don't play the fool with me.
I know you'll be sad when Felicia\nreturns to her village. Do you deny it?
My objective was to return her to her\nvillage. Why would I be sad about\naccomplishing my goal?
You won't recognize it unless someone\nelse spells it out, huh? Fine, then.
See, this whole time I thought there\nwas something off about all of this,\nand then I remembered a story.

It was about a dragon who was sealed
away after being falsely accused of
destroying an entire kingdom.
...A dragon called Phantom.
Even though it was really the work of\na fiend, they said he was responsible.
Someone who had been through that\nwouldn't save humans without a reason.
I mean, the idea you'd risk everything\nfor some random woman is simply—
Cease the flapping of your gums,\nFlamewyrm! We are dragons;\nwe are a supreme race.
Ones such as us could never hold feelings\nof ＂love＂ for those below us.
You're saying a dragon can only love\nanother dragon?
Heh. Those are the words of someone\ndesperate to bury their own feelings.
Please...do not make me think further\non this fool's errand of a dream.
I mustn't desire to be with her...
Do you think that woman could be happy\nat the side of a hideous dragon such as I?

Oh, I have heard the chatter when my
back is turned. Others cast aspersions,
claiming I look as though a fiend has
disguised itself as a dragon.
They say I am the cause of calamity.\nOne such as that has no business\nwith her.
Oh, come on! This is pathetic!
You said it yourself, didn't you?\nDragons are a supreme race.
If you're so supreme, you shouldn't shoot\nyourself down before you've even given\nyourself a chance!
What are YOU talking about?\nI am a dragon, and she is sylvan!
Our worlds are completely different!\nLiving together would be...
Who cares how you're different?\nIf you want to be together, you should be!
We hold the power to do such a thing,\ndo we not?
I know we can't do as humans do\nand get married for our entire lives.
But we can't help how we feel\nif we want to be together!
That's why I've made up my mind to\nstick with my darling until the very end.
I'm going to be by his side to protect\nhim and the ones he loves.
It seems you are just as strong as the\nstories say.
Nothing is more powerful than a maiden\nwith love in her heart.
The simple act of loving someone\nMAKES you stronger.
I am unfamiliar with this particular\nway of thinking.
Now if you do not mind,\nI would like to be alone.
Well, I've said my piece, so I'll head\nback to be with my darling.
If you're really a dragon, then you\nshould face your feelings head-on.
But I don't... No. I cannot.
Good morning, Phantom.\nDid you sleep well?
...Yes. For today is the day\nyou finally return home.
The road has been long, but you\njust need a bit more patience.
Come on, everyone. Let's get going.
